The defendant Landuris Chae Marcel Steavens was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Theft-Business Setting <=$2500, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Received and filed: Defense counsel's notice of completion of representation.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant. 

Defendant sentenced to serve 4 MONTHS in the House of Correction, consecutive to any other sentence, with credit for 4 days time served.  COURT STAYED THE SENTENCE and placed the defendant on probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 12 MONTHS. If revoked, Court allows HUBER for work, school and treatment.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
     *   Mental Health Evaluation and take ALL prescribed
          medication, and/or any treatment deemed appropriate.          
     *   Defendant to participate in Alcohol and Drug Assessment
          and successfully complete recommended treatment.
     *   Successfully complete any other counseling and/or
          treatment deemed appropriate.
     *   Defendant to provide a DNA sample and pay the DNA surcharge.
     *   Court waives all non-mandatory fees and costs due to defendant's income.
     *   Pay all mandatory costs, fees, surcharges (including DNA surcharge)
          and restitution by the end of probation. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.
     *   Restitution is set at $950.00 payable to Whole Foods.

Upon successful completion of the sentence Court will allow for expungement.

Defendant Landuris Chae Marcel Steavens in court with attorney Robert J Hampton.  Jennifer L Pickett appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  

Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.
